description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Occupational Therapy provisions in Hertfordshire Secure Forensic Services have undergone transformation in line with the national Recovery College agenda. We are developing the provision of specialised Occupational Therapy assessment / intervention alongside embedding meaningful activity into the three forensic units across Hertfordshire. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The exciting opportunity has arisen for an Occupational Therapist to drive this change alongside the OT professional Lead. The successful applicant will also work closely with the MDT / rest of the recovery team including Occupational Therapy Technical Instructors and other recovery team staff to ensure that a high quality, person centred service is provided for people in services. This post will be based in our low secure Mental Health unit&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Herts Secure Services offers assessment and treatment in a Medium (MSU) and Low&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;secure (LSU) setting to individuals who have a history of offending behaviour. The&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;services consist of 30 beds in the Learning Disability MSU, 9 beds in the Learning&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Disability in LSU and 15 in the Mental Health LSU.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;All patients are detained under the Mental Health Act 1983 and have complex health&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;needs. Referrals come mainly via the courts and prisons but also from other health&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;settings e.g. special hospitals or other secure environments&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As a proactive clinician you will manage a clinical caseload and carrying out comprehensive assessments and deliver evidence based interventions, using the Model of Human Occupation. This supports assessment, collaborative treatment planning, care planning in accordance with the Care Programme Approach and structured outcome measurement. Within this role the post holder will deliver and individual / group sessions focused on purposeful and meaningful activities to help the individual achieve their personal and recovery goals as well as support to carers.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameLisa FordJob titleProfessional Lead OT for Forensic ServicesEmail addresslisa.ford6@nhs.netTelephone number01923 684602Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Visits to the units would be advisable&lt;/p&gt;
